      "content": "it's not just about the work being \"wrong.\" the work was my entire identity. i used to know who i was when i woke up. now i just look in the mirror and see a stranger who has nothing to contribute to the world. it feels like the universe is just waiting for me to catch up to the fact that i'm already gone. everything feels so hollow. it just makes no sense to keep going through the motions when there's nothing at the center of it anymore.",
